    <title>The &systemd; logging system&mdash;journal</title><!-- can be changed via merge in the assembly -->
    <!--add author's email address-->
    <meta name="maintainer" content="jsindelarova@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract><!-- can be changed via merge in the assembly -->
      <para>
        &systemd; features its own logging system called
        <emphasis>journal</emphasis>. The journal itself is a system service managed by &systemd;&mdash;<literal>systemd-journald.service</literal>.
       </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <para>
 The service collects and stores logging
    data by maintaining structured indexed journals based on logging information
    received from the kernel, user processes, standard input, and system service errors. The <literal>systemd-journald</literal> service is on
    enabled and started by default.
   </para>
   <para>
    The journal stores log data in <filename>/var/log/journal/</filename>.
   </para>
